<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
1. Wing with grey to brown stigma at end of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[604,611,1433,1445]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">1</subScript>
; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[642,663,1433,1445]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">4+5</subScript>
thickened from basal quarter onwards (
<figureCitation box="[447,529,1450,1471]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[541,566,1450,1471]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[148,192,2106,2127]" captionTargetBox="[167,1500,731,2053]" captionTargetId="figure-9@8.[137,1543,712,2083]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 20–24. Hercostomus limosus, new species, male: 20, wing; 21, antenna; 22, male genitalia; 23, cercus; 24, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339239/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">20</figureCitation>
) ........................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" box="[126,765,1479,1502]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead box="[126,765,1479,1502]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
– Wing without stigma; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[400,422,1490,1502]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">4+5</subScript>
not thickened ............................ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
2. Stigma elongate, extending beyond start of thickening of vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[179,201,1548,1560]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">4+5</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[217,291,1536,1557]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with small denticle, in a more basal position (
<figureCitation box="[256,329,1565,1586]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); knee hind femur darkened above .............. .................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[492,634,1594,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolatus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[492,634,1594,1615]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">H. lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[648,764,1594,1615]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
– Stigma shorter, reaching the level of thickening of vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[695,716,1634,1646]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">4+5</subScript>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[148,192,2106,2127]" captionTargetBox="[167,1500,731,2053]" captionTargetId="figure-9@8.[137,1543,712,2083]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 20–24. Hercostomus limosus, new species, male: 20, wing; 21, antenna; 22, male genitalia; 23, cercus; 24, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339239/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
); aedaegus with a larger denticle in a more anteriad position (
<figureCitation box="[171,244,1680,1701]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[148,192,2106,2127]" captionTargetBox="[167,1500,731,2053]" captionTargetId="figure-9@8.[137,1543,712,2083]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 20–24. Hercostomus limosus, new species, male: 20, wing; 21, antenna; 22, male genitalia; 23, cercus; 24, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339239/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); knee hind femur not darkened above ...................... .......................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[529,633,1709,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limosus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[529,633,1709,1730]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">H. limosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[648,764,1709,1730]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
3. First flagellomere distinctly elongated, at least 2.0 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[253,321,1767,1788]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[150,194,2105,2126]" captionTargetBox="[162,1474,999,2064]" captionTargetId="figure-9@2.[141,1510,973,2085]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–3. Hercostomus brevidigitalis, new species, male: 1, antenna; 2, male genitalia; 3, cercus. iel, inner epandrial lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[335,360,1767,1788]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[126,170,2107,2128]" captionTargetBox="[130,1466,782,2038]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[118,1493,750,2065]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 25–28. Hercostomus meieri, new species, male: 25, antenna; 26, male genitalia; 27, hypandrium and aedeagus, ventral view; 28, cercus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339241" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">25</figureCitation>
) ............................................................ 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">– First flagellomere not elongated, at most 1.6 times as long as wide ....................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
4. First flagellomere 2.3 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[600,656,1853,1874]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[150,194,2105,2126]" captionTargetBox="[162,1474,999,2064]" captionTargetId="figure-9@2.[141,1510,973,2085]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–3. Hercostomus brevidigitalis, new species, male: 1, antenna; 2, male genitalia; 3, cercus. iel, inner epandrial lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); all coxae blackish; femora blackish except tip of fore and mid femora; cercus with 3 strong bristles on outer margin ......................... ................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[475,634,1940,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevidigitalis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[475,634,1940,1961]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">H. brevidigitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[647,764,1940,1961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[126,765,1421,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
– First flagellomere distinctly elongated, 3.0 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[171,241,1997,2018]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[126,170,2107,2128]" captionTargetBox="[130,1466,782,2038]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[118,1493,750,2065]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 25–28. Hercostomus meieri, new species, male: 25, antenna; 26, male genitalia; 27, hypandrium and aedeagus, ventral view; 28, cercus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339241" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brown, femora yellow; cercus without strong bristles on outer margin .......... ............................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[541,633,2055,2076]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meieri" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[541,633,2055,2076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">H. meieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[647,764,2055,2076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
