<figureCitation box="[1043,1102,205,226]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[126,170,2077,2098]" captionTargetBox="[143,1453,419,2030]" captionTargetId="figure-86@3.[115,1485,399,2060]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–10. Hercostomus singaporensis, new species, male: 4, wing; 5, antenna; 6, apex of fore tibia and tarsomere 1 (anterior lateral view); 7, apex of mid tibia and tarsomere 1 (posterior view); 8, male genitalia; 9, cercus; 10, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) shortened, concave ventrally with 2 long curved ventral bristles; mid tarsomere 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1313,1371,234,255]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[126,170,2077,2098]" captionTargetBox="[143,1453,419,2030]" captionTargetId="figure-86@3.[115,1485,399,2060]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–10. Hercostomus singaporensis, new species, male: 4, wing; 5, antenna; 6, apex of fore tibia and tarsomere 1 (anterior lateral view); 7, apex of mid tibia and tarsomere 1 (posterior view); 8, male genitalia; 9, cercus; 10, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
